I assume that your professor wants you to change `counter` to an [`AtomicInteger`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/atomic/AtomicInteger.html). First you want to import `AtomicInteger` as well as change the declaration of `counter` and the constructor to reflect that.
```java
import java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;
```
```java
public GarageWorker(int initialCarCount) {
    counter = new AtomicInteger(initialCarCount);
}

public AtomicInteger counter;
```
Also, you want to change the `increaseVehicleCount` and `decreaseVehicleCount` methods in order to use `AtomicInteger` instead of `int`.
```java
public int increaseVehicleCount() {
    return counter.incrementAndGet();
}
```
```java
public int decreaseVehicleCount() {
    return counter.decrementAndGet();
}
```
[`incrementAndGet`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/atomic/AtomicInteger.html#incrementAndGet--) as well as [`decrementAndGet`](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/atomic/AtomicInteger.html#decrementAndGet--) do just as they say: they increment (or decrement) and subsequently returns the new value. For more information, take a look at [the Javadoc](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/concurrent/atomic/AtomicInteger.html).

Cheers!

