Although its common for proxies to just be passed like `IP:PORT` or `USER:PASS:IP:PORT`, you need to reformat those proxies so that requests understands how to connect:

https://requests.kennethreitz.org/en/master/user/advanced/#proxies

Your proxy dict should resemble:

```python3
proxies={
    &#39;http&#39;: &#39;http://0.0.0.0:0000&#39;,
    &#39;https&#39;: &#39;https://0.0.0.0:0000&#39;
}
```

Note that if you have user-pass authenticated proxies, they need to be reformatted like: `proxies = {&#39;http&#39;: &#39;http://user:pass@10.10.1.10:3128/&#39;}`

